{{short description|Moroccan public official}}
An '''[https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Droit_musulman#L'adel adel]''' or '''adoul''' is a type of public official in Morocco. Adels act in pairs to record marriages. They may also draft contracts, prenuptial agreements, divorce settlements and adjudicate testaments. Their office is comparable to that of a [[civil law notary]]. Women were first allowed to become adels in 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/afrique/article/2018/01/23/le-maroc-autorise-les-femmes-a-exercer-le-metier-de-notaire-de-droit-musulman_5245853_3212.html|title=Le Maroc autorise les femmes à exercer le métier de notaire de droit musulman|work=Le Monde|language=French | date=23 January 2018|access-date=12 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2018/09/254339/women-adoul-morocco-public-notary/|title=Women Adoul in Morocco: The Not So Modern Legal Dilemma|first=Ihsane Elidrissi | last=Elhassani|work=Morocco World News|date=30 September 2018|access-date=12 October 2018}}</ref><ref name="tribune">{{cite news |title=Driss Alami : La profession de Adel ouverte aux femmes, conforte l’égalité des genres |url=https://lnt.ma/driss-alami-profession-de-adel-ouverte-aux-femmes-conforte-legalite-genres/ |accessdate=12 October 2018 |work=La Tribune |date=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref>http://www.consulat.ma/an/prestation_for.cfm?gr_id=22&id=446</ref>

