{{Morocco-stub}}

The '''duty to defend''' is a [[liability insurance|liability insurer]]'s [[duty]] to defend the insured against claims. It is generally broader than the duty to [[indemnity|indemnify]] and may cover defense against claims where ultimately no damage is awarded, and possibly even against claims that would not be covered by the duty to idemnify.<ref name="IRMI">{{cite web|url=https://www.irmi.com/online/insurance-glossary/terms/d/duty-to-defend.aspx |title= Glossary of insurance & risk management terms: duty to defend |publisher=IRMI |accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref> It covers both civil suits and alternative dispute resolution procedures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanbar.org/groups/young_lawyers/publications/the_101_201_practice_series/duty.html |title=The duty to defend: What insurers, insureds and their counsel need to know when faced with a liability coverage dispute |publisher=[[American Bar Association]] |first=Eliot M. |last=Harris |accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref> In American courts disputes regarding the application of the duty to defend are generally resolved in the insured's favor.<ref name="IRMI" />

